	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><add>Hebrew</add></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date>May 19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1857</date></p>
				<p>My Dear Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I expected ere this my last commu<lb/>nication would have appeared in your periodical<lb/> as the one of the Jewish Chronicle which was <lb/>sent same time after yours has already met<lb/> with attention.  I am at a loss to know the<lb/> cause as I replied to your note also relative<lb/> to my being appointed your agent here and<lb/> my views thereon.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">There is nothing of importance<lb/> stirring here in Jewish matters&#44; the sister con<lb/>gregation is expecting the <persName>Revd Alexr B. Davis</persName><lb/> from <placeName>London</placeName>&#44; lately of <placeName>Portsea&#44; Portsmouth</placeName><lb/> to undertake the duties of the ministry&#44; he is<lb/> said to be in the expected packet due on <date>Sun<lb/>day the 21<hi rend="sup">st</hi></date>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">In my last letter I took the liber<lb/>ty of soliciting the aid of your services to procure<lb/> for me a few books for which on my being<lb/> acquainted with the cost I shall remit you the<lb/> money through a house in <placeName>New York</placeName>. Viz.<lb/> <persName>Salomon&#39;s</persName> Lectures</p>
				<p><persName>Dias&#39;s</persName> Letters in the evidences of Christianity 3 sets the<lb/> Hebrew spelling Books 6 copies whole series in each <sic>sett</sic><lb/> Catechisms for young children 6 <add>&#63;</add></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have sent you <del>a</del> newspaper<lb/> reports of my sermon on <add>Hebrew</add> which you can<lb/> make use of&#44; and as a friend and brother in<lb/> <placeName>Israel</placeName>&#44; should you know of any works calcula</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>ted to benefit me in my new sphere of duties I<lb/> should feel it an obligation should you advise me<lb/> of them.  I shall in return be most happy to render<lb/> you what service I can in <placeName>Jamaica</placeName> as far<lb/> as lies in my power to do so.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I am endeavoring as much as<lb/> possible to bring round Synagogue matters&#44; and<lb/> there seems to be some visible improvements&#44; but<lb/> it requires active labors to be at all times pre<lb/>pared to satisfy <hi rend="underline">all parties</hi>.  I have given up<lb/> the school&#44; as my desire is to give all my<lb/> attention to my ministerial duties&#44; which are<lb/> rather arduous&#44; as I have now added to them<lb/> since the old Hazan&#39;s death</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Let me hear speedily from you<lb/> as I should like my order satisfied at your very<lb/> earliest convenience.  Accept my devoted regards<lb/> for your welfare and prosperity and believe<lb/> me to be</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">Your faithful Servant</p>
			<p rend="indent(11)"><persName role="author">A Delevante</persName></p>
				<p>To the <addressee>Revrd. Is&#58; Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
				<p>PS. I have had no Occident for the last three months<lb/> this you will be pleased to notice and en<lb/>deavor to remedy as should I get an<lb/> answer to <hi rend="underline">my letter of 3 months past with Jewish</hi><lb/> <hi rend="underline">intelligence</hi> I should look about seeking subscribers</p>
